The paper deals with the study of covering numbers of the space of convex functions, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves the study of convergence rates of empirical minimization procedures, which is a topic in numerical analysis (cs.NA). The study of convex functions is also relevant in computational geometry (cs.CG) and theoretical computer science (cs.CC).
